      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "19699e9e-1e37-4b0c-a27c-9420bea077ca",
      "text": "Recently, there has been a movement towards greater transparency in the fields of policy and technology. Jasanoff comes to the conclusion that there is no longer a question of if there needs to be increased public participation in making decisions about science and technology, but now there needs to be ways to make a more meaningful conversation between the public and those developing the technology.[https://link.springer.com/article/10.1023%2FA%3A1025557512320 Technologies of Humility: Citizen Participation in Governing Science]"
